Diamond::

She looked at him and let her arms fall to her side. "It's nothing. 
It was just hooked up to that one cuff. It's nothing.  I just have to 
disconnect them and I'll be ok."

She breathed a small sigh of relief when he threw the cuffs away.  
She wasn't certain of the Council's abbility to track with those 
things. She felt reasonably sure that she was out of the range of the 
Council, but wanted to make sure by having the cuffs destroyed.

"I just have to have the wires cut and the small openeing closed. 
Nothing to worry about."
